e since the stock began trading more than a decade ago. JetBlue climbed 4.9=
%.
JetBlue and Spirit contended that consolidation is the only way smaller air=
lines can effectively compete with the dominant carriers. In a joint statem=
ent, the companies said they =E2=80=9Care evaluating our next steps as part=
 of the legal process.=E2=80=9D

Here is  the judge=E2=80=99s opinion. And here is  the press release that S=
pirit put out in June 2022, saying =E2=80=9CSpirit Airlines Reaffirms Commi=
tment to Merger with Frontier=E2=80=9D and arguing that =E2=80=9Cthe latest=
 offer from JetBlue does nothing to address our Board=E2=80=99s serious con=
cerns that a combination with them would not receive regulatory approval.=
=E2=80=9D Spirit had a deal with Frontier Group Holdings Inc., another ultr=
a-low-cost carrier, but then it got a cash bid from JetBlue that shareholde=
rs preferred.
The board thought this was a mistake, because the JetBlue deal would not go=
 through. It argued this vehemently, but it lost the argument: The Frontier=
 deal required shareholder approval, and it=C2=A0was clear that shareholder=
s would not approve it because they wanted JetBlue=E2=80=99s cash. So in Ju=
