ations, back in the good times,=C2=A0and now they need to raise money again=
. It is, for some combination of good and bad reasons, extremely undesirabl=
e for a startup that raised money at $1 billion to raise money again at $50=
0 million. Therefore there is a business opportunity for a fund that will:
=09Give startups money at a $500 million valuation, but=09
Say=C2=A0that it=E2=80=99s at a $1 billion valuation.

This is called =E2=80=9Cstructure,=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9Cstructured equity.=
=E2=80=9D=C2=A0Bloomberg=E2=80=99s Gillian Tan  reported Friday:

