<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Oh <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusin=
ess.com/click/34031994.258404/aHR0cHM6Ly9uZXdzLmJsb29tYmVyZ2xhdy5jb20vZXNnL=
25ldy1oYW1wc2hpcmUtZ29wLW9mZmljaWFscy1zZWVrLXRvLW1ha2UtdXNpbmctZXNnLWEtY3Jp=
bWU/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBd3065cb5" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"=
itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none=
 !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border=
-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  sure whatever</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Republican lawmakers in New Hampshire are seek=
ing to make using ESG criteria in state funds a crime in the latest attack =
on the beleaguered investing strategy.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Representatives led by=C2=A0Mike Belcher=C2=A0=
introduced=C2=A0a bill=C2=A0that would prohibit the state=E2=80=99s treasur=
y, pension fund and executive branch from using investments that consider e=
nvironmental, social and governance factors. =E2=80=9CKnowingly=E2=80=9D vi=
olating the law would be a felony punishable by not less than one year and =
no more than 20 years imprisonment, according to the proposal.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Pensions &amp; Investments <a href=3D"https://=
link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34031994.258404/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cucGlvb=
mxpbmUuY29tL2VzZy9uZXctaGFtcHNoaXJlLWJpbGwtd291bGQtbWFrZS1pdC1mZWxvbnkta25v=
d2luZ2x5LXVzZS1lc2ctY3JpdGVyaWEtaW52ZXN0aW5nLXRheHBheWVyLWRvbGxhcnM/607f07c=
eef4b8524a319a23cB023cf43e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" =
target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important=
; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-sty=
le: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> reports</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">"Executive branch agencies that are permitted =
to invest funds shall review their investments and pursue any necessary ste=
ps to ensure that no funds or state-controlled investments are invested wit=
h firms that invest New Hampshire funds in accounts with any regard whatsoe=
ver based on environmental, social, and governance criteria," the bill said=
.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The New Hampshire Retirement System "shall adh=
ere to their fiduciary obligation and not invest with any firm that will in=
vest state retirement system funds in investment funds that consider enviro=
nmental, social, and governance criteria, as the investment goal should be =
to obtain the highest return on investment for New Hampshire's taxpayers an=
d retirees," the bill said.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Investors aren=E2=80=99t allowed to=C2=A0<em>c=
onsider governance</em>! Imagine if this was the law; imagine if it was a f=
elony for an investment manager to consider governance =E2=80=9Cwith any re=
gard whatsoever.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusin=
ess.com/click/34031994.258404/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL=
2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDEtMTYvbW9yZ2FuLXN0YW5sZXktbGVha2VkLXNvbWUtYmxvY2stdHJh=
ZGVzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAxMTcyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJ=
jZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDExNyZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607=
f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBae2eb7aa" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsco=
pe" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impor=
tant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom=
-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  talked yesterday</a> about Elon M=
usk=E2=80=99s plans to extort billions of dollars of free stock out of Tesl=
a Inc. by (1) owning a big chunk of Tesla stock, (2)=C2=A0<em>selling=C2=A0=
</em>a lot of that stock to raise money to pursue his distracting personal =
hobbies, and then (3) telling Tesla=E2=80=99s board =E2=80=9Cwell, you know=
, I don=E2=80=99t own enough Tesla stock to really make it worth my while t=
o work on Tesla; if you want me to do my job as CEO you=E2=80=99d better do=
uble my stake to keep me motivated.=E2=80=9D Unless the board gives him a t=
on more stock, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/340=
31994.258404/aHR0cHM6Ly90d2l0dGVyLmNvbS9lbG9ubXVzay9zdGF0dXMvMTc0Njk5OTQ4OD=
I1MjcwMzA5OA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB0ab8efb1" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" item=
scope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decorat=
ion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00000=
0; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">he posted</a>, =E2=
=80=9CI would prefer to build products outside of Tesla.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That=E2=80=99s (1) absolutely <a href=3D"https=
://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34031994.258404/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3=
NqLmNvbS9idXNpbmVzcy9hdXRvcy9hLTYwLXBsdXMtYmlsbGlvbi1wYXktcGFja2FnZS1tdXNrL=
WdpdmVzLXRlc2xhcy1ib2FyZC1hLW5pZ2h0bWFyZS10YXNrLWJiOTczMmU1P21vZD1ocF9saXN0=
Yl9wb3My/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBa0af551f" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscop=
e=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration:=
 none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; b=
order-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">crazy corporate governa=
nce</a> and also (2) just a typical Tuesday in wild Tesla corporate governa=
nce news.=C2=A0Tesla is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/=
click/34031994.258404/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnl0aW1lcy5jb20vMjAyMy8wMi8yMS9idXNpb=
mVzcy9lbG9uLW11c2stdGVzbGEtcGF5LXN1aXQuaHRtbA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBde0c=
5868" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" styl=
e=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width:=
 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-=
color: #ccc;"> currently being sued</a> over Musk=E2=80=99s=C2=A0<em>previo=
us </em>enormous pay package, which was supposed to motivate him to pay att=
ention to Tesla, but which in fact just gave him enough stock to sell to ra=
ise money to distract himself with Twitter.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you are a big Tesla shareholder, it might b=
e reasonable to say something like =E2=80=9Cwell, I like what Musk has done=
 for the place, but I wish the board would try to rein him in,=E2=80=9D and=
 try to set up a meeting with the Tesla board to discuss possible ways to s=
top giving him more stock. Or it might be reasonable to say =E2=80=9Cwell, =
I like what Musk has done for the place so far, but I=E2=80=99m increasingl=
y worried that the governance problems here are going to reduce its long-te=
rm value =E2=80=94=C2=A0what if Musk is <em>telling the truth </em>about bu=
ilding products outside of Tesla? =E2=80=94=C2=A0so I=E2=80=99m just going =
to sell the stock.=E2=80=9D Both of these approaches =E2=80=94=C2=A0meeting=
 with the board to try to improve governance to increase the long-term valu=
e of the company, or selling stock because you are worried that bad governa=
nce will lower the long-term value of the company =E2=80=94=C2=A0are totall=
y normal things for responsible investment managers to do.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Unless they run money for New Hampshire, in wh=
ich case this might become a felony? Believe me, if it does, Elon Musk will=
 hear about it.</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Investor:</strong> Elon, thanks for me=
eting with us. I=E2=80=99m worried that you keep demanding tens of billions=
 of dollars of stock awards, selling the stock to buy distracting toys, and=
 then extracting more stock by threatening to spend more time with the toys=
. Could you just try to focus a bit more on doing your job as CEO of Tesla?=
</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Musk: </strong>I=E2=80=99m calling the=
 police! You considered governance! You=E2=80=99re going to prison for 20 y=
ears!</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I=E2=80=99m sorry, this is so stupid. =E2=80=
=9CESG=E2=80=9D is <em>essentially=C2=A0</em>about considering certain risk=
s to a company=E2=80=99s financial results: You might want to avoid investi=
ng in a company if its factories are going to be washed away by rising ocea=
ns, or if its main product is going to be regulated out of existence, or if=
 its <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34031994.2584=
04/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnl0aW1lcy5jb20vYXJ0aWNsZS9idWQtbGlnaHQtYm95Y290dC5odG1s=
/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB1ec38f66" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"ite=
mscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !i=
mportant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bo=
ttom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> position on controversial soci=
al issues will cost it sales</a>, or if its CEO controls the board and spen=
ds too much corporate money on wasteful personal projects. Obviously ESG in=
 practice is also other, more controversial things:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">If you care about the environment, so=
cial issues, etc., you might want to invest in companies that you think are=
 environmentally or socially good, whether or not they are good financial i=
nvestments.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You might incorrectly =
convince yourself that the stuff you think is environmentally or socially g=
ood is also good for the bottom line: You might have a wishful estimate of =
how quickly the world will transition away from fossil fuels, to justify yo=
ur desire not to invest in oil companies. You might tell yourself =E2=80=9C=
this company=E2=80=99s stance on social issues will cost it lots of custome=
rs=E2=80=9D when really the customers don=E2=80=99t care, but you do.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But if you <em>make it a crime for investors t=
o consider certain financial risks=C2=A0</em>then you get too much of those=
 risks.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In particular, I suspect, you get too much gov=
ernance risk. If every investor tomorrow said =E2=80=9Cokay we don=E2=80=99=
t care about the environment,=E2=80=9D most companies probably wouldn=E2=80=
=99t ramp up their pollution: Their executives probably don=E2=80=99t=C2=A0=
<em>want=C2=A0</em>to pollute unnecessarily, polluting probably wouldn=E2=
=80=99t help the bottom line, and many companies just sit at computers deve=
loping software and couldn=E2=80=99t pollute much if they wanted to. But if=
 every investor tomorrow said =E2=80=9Cokay we don=E2=80=99t care about gov=
ernance,=E2=80=9D then, I mean, =E2=80=9Cgovernance=E2=80=9D is just a way =
of saying =E2=80=9Csomebody makes sure that the CEO is doing a good job and=
 doesn=E2=80=99t pay herself too much.=E2=80=9D If the investors don=E2=80=
=99t care about that, then a lot of CEOs will be happy to give themselves r=
aises and spend more time <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.co=
m/click/34031994.258404/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9idXNpbmVzcy90aGUtNjUtbWl=
sbGlvbi1wZXJrLWZvci1jZW9zLXBlcnNvbmFsLXVzZS1vZi10aGUtY29ycG9yYXRlLWpldC1oYX=
Mtc29hcmVkLWJjMjBhOTg4/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB1b5f5d42" itemprop=3D"Story=
Link" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; te=
xt-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-col=
or: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> on the c=
orporate jet to their vacation homes</a>.</p>
