" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-d=
ecoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: =
#000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  the takeove=
r fight</a> over Sculptor Capital Management Inc. Basically:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Sculptor had a deal to sell itself to=
 another asset management firm, Rithm Capital Corp., for cash.</li>=09<li s=
tyle=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">It then got another, higher cash bid from a co=
alition of hedge fund managers, led by Boaz Weinstein, who wanted to buy Sc=
ulptor.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Sculptor=E2=80=99s board o=
f directors said =E2=80=9Clook, we know the Weinstein bid=C2=A0<em>looks=C2=
=A0</em>higher, but we think that if we sign that deal it won=E2=80=99t act=
ually close. Clients will flee, which will give Weinstein a way out of the =
deal, which he=E2=80=99ll take, and we=E2=80=99ll be left with nothing. And=
 it will be crippling for the firm to sign a deal and lose it. We should st=
ick with the lower, safer deal that we think will close.=E2=80=9D</li>=09<l=
i style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Sculptor shareholders largely did not belie=
ve this, the stock traded above the Rithm deal price, and there was pressur=
e on the board to take the Weinstein deal.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-botto=
m: 5px;">Eventually Sculptor managed to get Rithm=E2=80=99s price up to a l=
evel that was competitive with Weinstein=E2=80=99s, it=C2=A0<a href=3D"http=
s://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34031994.258404/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuY=
mxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMTAtMTgvb2YtY291cnNlLXNjdWxw=
dG9yLWdvdC1zdWVkP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAxMTcyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWw=
mdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDExNyZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZX=
lzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB6aa03ff2" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscop=
e=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration:=
 none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; b=
order-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">did some shenanigans</a=
> to lock up the vote, and the Rithm deal closed.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The question, ultimately, was: Did Sculptor=E2=
=80=99s board of directors know better than its shareholders? The sharehold=
ers, looking at a choice between two prices, wanted the higher price. The b=
oard, more deeply involved in the negotiations (but also more conflicted), =
said =E2=80=9Cno, you don=E2=80=99t understand, the higher price is not rea=
l, you won=E2=80=99t get it, trust us.=E2=80=9D It is the board=E2=80=99s j=
ob to make decisions on behalf of shareholders, sometimes even decisions th=
e shareholders don=E2=80=99t like. But the board is limited in its power, a=
nd sometimes those decisions have to go to a shareholder vote, and you can =
get an awkward situation where the board is sure that one choice is right, =
but the shareholders will only approve the other one.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Sculptor=E2=80=99s board worked it out. Spirit=
 Airlines=E2=80=99 did not, as=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergb=
usiness.com/click/34031994.258404/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL=
2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDEtMTYvamV0Ymx1ZS1zcGlyaXQtZGVhbC1ibG9ja2VkLWJ5LWp1ZGdl=
LW9uLWFudGl0cnVzdC1ncm91bmRzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAxMTcyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWR=
pdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDExNyZ1dG1fY2FtcG=
FpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB1122d6b1" itemprop=3D"StoryLi=
nk" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text=
-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color=
: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Bloomberg N=
ews reports</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A federal judge blocked JetBlue Airways Corp.=
=E2=80=99s $3.8 billion acquisition of Spirit Airlines Inc., saying the com=
bination would stifle competition and raise fares for consumers.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">US District Judge William G. Young sided with =
the federal government and said the merger would harm cost-conscious travel=
ers by eliminating the nation=E2=80=99s dominant deep-fare discount airline=
 and drive up prices across the industry.=C2=A0=E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Spirit=E2=80=99s shares plunged 47% Tuesday in=
 New York, the biggest decline since the stock began trading more than a de=
cade ago. JetBlue climbed 4.9%.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">JetBlue and Spirit contended that consolidatio=
n is the only way smaller airlines can effectively compete with the dominan=
t carriers. In a joint statement, the companies said they =E2=80=9Care eval=
uating our next steps as part of the legal process.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/34031994.258404/aHR0cHM6Ly9hc3NldHMuYndieC5pby9kb2N1bWVu=
dHMvdXNlcnMvaXFqV0hCRmRmeElVL3JPbDd4NFliU0pqMC92MA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23c=
B6064ca38" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank"=
 style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-w=
idth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgr=
ound-color: #ccc;"> the judge=E2=80=99s opinion</a>. And here is <a href=3D=
"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34031994.258404/aHR0cHM6Ly93=
d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE0OTg3MTAvMDAwMTQ5ODcxMDIyMDAwMjc=
yL3NwaXJpdGNvbW1lbnRzb25qZXRibHVlci5odG0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc2148db8"=
 itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"=
color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px;=
 border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color=
: #ccc;"> the press release</a> that Spirit put out in June 2022, saying =
=E2=80=9CSpirit Airlines Reaffirms Commitment to Merger with Frontier=E2=80=
=9D and arguing that =E2=80=9Cthe latest offer from JetBlue does nothing to=
 address our Board=E2=80=99s serious concerns that a combination with them =
would not receive regulatory approval.=E2=80=9D Spirit had a deal with Fron=
tier Group Holdings Inc., another ultra-low-cost carrier, but then it got a=
 cash bid from JetBlue that shareholders preferred.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The board thought this was a mistake, because =
the JetBlue deal would not go through. It argued this vehemently, but it lo=
st the argument: The Frontier deal required shareholder approval, and it=C2=
=A0was clear that shareholders would not approve it because they wanted Jet=
Blue=E2=80=99s cash. So in July 2022, Spirit=E2=80=99s board caved and <a h=
ref=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34031994.258404/aHR0cH=
