rs to buy stakes in venture capital-backed technology start-ups, as a long =
drought in acquisitions and initial public offerings forces early investors=
 to offload their stock at discounts.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The start-up secondary market, where investors=
 and employees buy and sell tens of billions of dollars=E2=80=99 worth of s=
hares in privately held companies, is becoming an increasingly important tr=
ading venue, in the absence of traditional ways of cashing out and given a =
slowdown in start-up funding.</p>
